From d394a29decf8eca2b2ce4fb6070fe6320db84c3b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sun, 28 Jun 2026 21:32:42 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add desktop notifications popover to sidebar bell

Replace the sidebar bell's navigate-to-Meldinger behavior with a modern
notifications panel. Clicking the bell now opens a popover that lists recent
customer messages grouped by conversation, with unread highlighting, an exact
unread badge, a "mark all as read" action, realtime updates, loading
skeletons, an empty state, and a footer link to the full inbox. Selecting a
conversation deep-links to /meldinger?kunde=<id> and marks that thread read.

- hooks/use-notifications.ts: live customer-message notifications plus an
  exact unread count, kept in sync via a realtime subscription, with
  markAllRead/markThreadRead actions. Feature-gated through `enabled`.
- components/notifications-popover.tsx: the desktop popover UI.
- components/app-sidebar.tsx: render the popover from the bell and drive the
  collapsed-state dot and badge from the same hook.
- app/meldinger/{page,inbox-client}.tsx: honour ?kunde=<id> to pre-select a
  conversation on load.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
